{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/learning-disabilities/background-information/risk-factors/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"432f94cd-ae01-5de8-aedc-0b0ca066f01b","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field db90af05-6842-4a4f-92e3-a97300ca65d3 --><h2>What causes it?</h2><!-- end field db90af05-6842-4a4f-92e3-a97300ca65d3 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a67e1c12-15df-4d5f-8c5f-a97300ca38dd --><!-- begin field 5d486a8c-8fce-460e-ae0e-a97300ca65d3 --><ul><li><strong>Risk factors for the development of a learning disability include:</strong><ul><li>Some chromosomal and genetic anomalies — such as Down's syndrome, William's syndrome, Rhett syndrome, fragile X syndrome.</li><li>Some non-genetic congenital malformations — such as some types of spina bifida, hydrocephalus, microcephaly.</li><li>Prenatal exposures — including alcohol, sodium valproate, congenital rubella infection, zika virus.</li><li>Birth complications resulting in hypoxic brain injury/cerebral palsy.</li><li>Extreme prematurity (usually <33 weeks' gestation).</li><li>Childhood illness — such as meningitis, encephalitis, measles.</li><li>Childhood brain injury caused by accident/physical abuse.</li><li>Childhood neglect and/or lack of stimulation in early life.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Neurodevelopmental disorders that may be associated with a learning disability include autism spectrum disorder (ASD) and attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD).</strong></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">MHRA, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">NICE, 2016a</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">PHE, 2016b</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">NHS, 2017</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">Mental Health Foundation, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/learning-disabilities/references/\">PHE, 2018</a>]</p><!-- end field 5d486a8c-8fce-460e-ae0e-a97300ca65d3 --><!-- end item a67e1c12-15df-4d5f-8c5f-a97300ca38dd -->","topic":{"id":"81b6bf13-1851-5aca-a415-deb2664fff5b","topicId":"9cc09e0b-a51c-445a-a0f0-a8e200bd3e76","topicName":"Learning disabilities","slug":"learning-disabilities","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2020","chapters":[{"id":"433a4d95-fb0e-597f-886b-7a5bba677e2e","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e6952a3b-5351-51c3-b34d-3ce4fd90e136","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cd675bbe-842b-5eac-9101-92f52a07ffd0","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"42e6170c-2ad4-5c42-98b5-66bb0f315b56","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"cdef379f-d2ef-5c80-9644-6e1cb6864f2a","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"f8ff91d6-3a99-5f81-ab3e-b522150de1f1","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"dbf4d83d-021c-5c6c-8be4-5637c384ed7b","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"73bb96cd-3d7f-50c7-8bd6-2c3f50a56d70","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"4e9fbda8-d558-51be-9f50-16e404570513","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"8a99509d-dcc3-52cf-be04-85ee2c4aad00","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"88e8dc33-8096-57aa-accc-3ec205effbe3","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"b9a8bf11-ca0b-51a0-a965-d5058c0bceca","slu